+	defer w.limiter.upload.Begin(w.sourceID)()

+	jobWithPayloadsMap := make(map[string][]jobWithPayload)
+	for _, job := range jobs {

+		key := p.AggregateKey()

+		return nil, fmt.Errorf("creating tmp directory: %w", err)
+	}

+	minFailedAt := payloads[0].FailedAtTime()

# Description

- Push error index metadata to object storage.
- Sorting strategy for efficient PageGroup filtering.
- Create files based on failed_at, and include both received_at and failed_at as columns.
- Following is the file structure:
   - `<bucket-name>/<source-id>/<year>-<month>-<date>/<hour>/<first-failed-at-in-seconds>_<first-failed-at-in-seconds>_<instance-id>.parquet`

## Linear Ticket

- https://linear.app/rudderstack/issue/PIPE-317/push-error-metadata-to-rudderstack-s3-in-parquet-format

## Security

- [x] The code changed/added as part of this pull request won't create any security issues with how the software is being used.
